title: Unexpected panic using xml-rs

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

body:
## Summary

This code:

``` rust
extern crate xml;
//
// Dependencies list from Cargo.toml:
// [dependencies]
// xml-rs = "0.3"
//
use xml::reader::{Events, EventReader, XmlEvent};
fn get_operation_name(e: &XmlEvent::StartElement) -> String {
}
```

causes rustc to exit with "unexpected panic".

**Compiler version** is rustc 1.7.0 (a5d1e7a59 2016-02-29).

**Platform** is Windows 8.1, 64-bit.

Possibly related to  #32335.
